    "title": "Paneer Bhurji",
    "link": "/bhurji",
    "image": null,
    "date": "21 Jan, 2017",
    "category": ["main"],
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://farm1.staticflickr.com/671/31566913314_9a07089685_o_d.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>This is the indian version of scrambled tofu: crumbled paneer with vegetables and spices. A very filling meal full of protein that takes 10 minutes from start to finish. A must try!</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>250 g paneer, crumbled</li>\n  <li>50 g onion (1/2 medium), chopped</li>\n  <li>1 small tomato (100g), chopped</li>\n  <li>Other vegetables to taste (like green peas), optional</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp coconut oil</li>\n  <li>1/4 tsp whole cumin</li>\n  <li>Red chili powder to taste</li>\n  <li>1/2 tsp turmeric</li>\n  <li>1/8 tsp garam masala or more to taste</li> \n  <li>Optional: 1/4 tsp kasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves)</li>  \n  <li>Fresh coriander</li>\n  <li>1/2 tbsp lemon juice</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Process</strong>\n    <ol>\n      <li>First, if the crumbled paneer is too dry, add a little bit of warm water to rehydrate it.</li>\n      <li>Melt the coconut oil over medium-high heat. Add the cumin seeds until they start popping. Then, add the onion with some salt and cook for 5 minutes until they are brown.</li>\n      <li>Once the onion is cooked, add the ginger and garlic. Cook for a minute.</li>\n      <li>Add the tomatoes and salt. Cook for two minutes until they the tomatoes are soft, then add the other spices. Mix well.</li>\n      <li>Add the paneer (drained if you were soaking it). Cook for 30-60 seconds. Add the kasuri methi if you are using it.</li>\n      <li>Garnish with lemon juice and coriander.</li>\n    </ol>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Nutritional information</strong>, <em>for a serving (recipe serves 2)</em>\n    <ul>\n      <li>466 kCal</li>\n      <li><strong>8.3 g net carbs</strong>, 2 g fiber, 10.2 g total carbs</li>\n      <li><strong>26 g protein</strong></li>\n      <li>36.6 g fat</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
    "excerpt": "This is the indian version of scrambled tofu: crumbled paneer with vegetables and spices. A very filling meal full of..."
