    "title": "Low-carb pancakes",
    "link": "/ketoPancakes",
    "image": null,
    "date": "16 Sep, 2016",
    "category": ["breakfast"],
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://farm1.staticflickr.com/442/31327314580_6d51d7a9e7_o_d.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>These pancakes are my new favorite! They are so thick and fluffy, are fast to make in the morning, and so delicious! I hope you enjoy them as much as me!</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>10 g of vanilla-flavored protein powder (1/3 of a serving)</li>\n  <li>1 egg</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp flax meal</li>\n  <li>A pinch of salt</li>\n  <li>2/3 tbsp of coconut oil or butter + 1/3 for cooking</li>\n  <li>1/2 tbsp vinegar</li>\n  <li>1/3 tsp baking soda</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Process</strong>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Melt the coconut oil or butter. Then mix with the egg and vinegar.</li>\n      <li>In a different bowl, mix all the dry ingredients.</li>\n      <li>Add the dry ingredients into the wet ones and mix.\n        <ul>\n          <li><em>If I make it ahead of time, I mix everything except the baking soda, and then mix it in thoroughly right before cooking.</em></li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li>Heat up a non-stick pan with oil or butter on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the batter and cook like regular pancakes: about 1-1.5 minutes on the first side until you have bubbles on the surface, then flip and cook another minute on the other side.</li>\n      <li>Serve with your favorite low-carb topping - in my case, low-carb blackberry jam &lt;3</li>\n    </ol>\n  </li>\n  <li>Nutritional info, _per serving (serves 1)\n    <ul>\n      <li>267 kCal</li>\n      <li>3.8 g total carbs, 1.9 g fiber, 1.8 g net carbs</li>\n      <li><strong>14.8 g protein</strong></li>\n      <li>21.9 g fat</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
    "excerpt": "These pancakes are my new favorite! They are so thick and fluffy, are fast to make in the morning, and..."
