    "title": "Tikka masala",
    "link": "/tikkaMasalaEng",
    "image": null,
    "date": "11 Apr, 2016",
    "category": ["main"],
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5583/31552267092_2b780b9375_o_d.jpg \" /></p>\n\n<p>Chicken Tikka Masala (that can also be made with paneer or tofu to keep it vegetarian) is one of the most typical dishes in indian restaurants. It has a thick onion and tomato sauce, spicy with a sweet touch, that is always a hit.</p>\n\n<p>On top of that, it is easier to make than it seems. It doesn’t require many ingredients, and it always comes out great. Try it!</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>700 g chicken or paneer tikka</li> \n  <li>4 peeled tomatoes (450 g or 3 cups)</li>\n  <li>1 chopped medium onion (110g)</li>\n  <li>3 garlic cloves, chopped, or 1 tsp garlic paste</li>\n  <li>2'5 cm minced ginger or 1.5 tsp ginger paste <i>(use 2/3 of the amount if making paneer or tofu tikka masala)</i></li>\n  <li>Stevia to taste (equivalent to 2 tbsp brown sugar)</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp tomato paste</li>\n  <li>2 tsp garam masala</li>\n  <li>1/4 tsp chili or to taste</li>\n  <li>2 tbsp oil or ghee</li>\n  <li>Optional: 4 tbsp heavy cream (or yoghurt). <i>(You can substitute it for coconut milk if you want a vegan Tikka Masala.)</i></li> \n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Process</strong>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Heat up the oil and fry the onions for 5 min.</li>\n      <li>Add the garlic and ginger and cook for 2 min.</li>\n      <li>Add the spices and mix around, cooking it for 30 seg.</li>\n      <li>Add the rest of the ingredients, cover and cook on low heat for 20 min.</li>\n      <li>Take off the heat and process the sauce until smooth. Add the cream or yoghurt, and then the chicken or paneer tikka.</li>\n      <li>Let everything boil together for a few minutes and serve with pilao rice.</li>\n    </ol>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Nutritional info</strong>, for 1/5 of the sauce (for information on the chicken/paneer/tofu tikka, visit the <a href=\"http://maria.recipes/tikkaEng\">tikka recipe</a>:\n    <ul>\n      <li>148 kCal</li>\n      <li><strong>5.1 g net carbs</strong>, 1.6 g fiber, 6.7 g total carbs**</li>\n      <li>1.4 g protein</li>\n      <li>13 g fat</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
